      "message": "OK, I see what you’re doing here.\n\nHere’s a better way to handle it: leave our own forwarding header in here, at Crashpad’s third_party/lss/lss.h. If it’s in Crashpad, it #includes the LSS header at the location it’ll be checked out in the Crashpad tree. If it’s in Chromium, it #includes the LSS header at the Chromium location.\n\nThen we can include everything at a natural third_party path in our own code, and leave it to the forwarding header to decide who to pass it on to for the implementation.",
